# webxdc template rule

Before coding, read and follow:

- `README.md` -> **Agent Required Reading: webxdc compatibility**
- <https://github.com/webxdc/website/blob/main/src-docs/faq/compat.md>
- `docs/README.md`
- `docs/SHADCN_SVELTE.md`

## Required constraints

- Do not use `document.cookie`; use `localStorage`.
- Do not rely on `unload`, `beforeunload`, `pagehide`; use `visibilitychange`.
- Do not rely on `<title>` or `document.title`; app title comes from `manifest.toml`.
- Do not use external links as essential UX flow; use embedded content or `mailto:` where needed.
- Do not use `data:` links as download mechanism; use `sendToChat()`.
- Avoid permission-dependent APIs unless host support is confirmed.
- Do not rely on `window.open()`, `alert()`, `prompt()`, `confirm()`.
- Prefer compatibility-safe JS; if using newer syntax/APIs, ensure transpilation/compatibility.

## Svelte/SvelteKit guidance

- Use Svelte 5 patterns used by this project (`$state`, `$props`, `$derived`).
- Keep shared logic in `src/lib/*` when practical.
- Preserve static build compatibility for webxdc (`adapter-static`, relative paths).

## shadcn-svelte guidance

- This project is based on shadcn-svelte:
  - https://shadcn-svelte.com
- Add components using:
  - `bun x shadcn-svelte@latest add <component>`
  - example: `bun x shadcn-svelte@latest add card`
- Component catalog:
  - https://shadcn-svelte.com/docs/components
- Prefer reusable components in `src/lib/components/ui/*`.
- Use existing `Button` and `Input` components where applicable.
- Treat `src/routes/example_+page.svelte` and other demos as behavior references, not visual blueprints.
- Adapt UI/UX to each request's product goals instead of reproducing demo look-and-feel by default.
- Do not mirror demo-specific styling/content hierarchy unless user explicitly asks for it.
- For any new UI component:
  - add `src/lib/components/ui/<name>/<name>.svelte`
  - add `src/lib/components/ui/<name>/index.ts`
- Update `docs/SHADCN_SVELTE.md` when adding/changing components.

## Example integrity requirements

Do not break the built-in demos in `src/routes/+page.svelte`:

- shared-state updates
- notify/reply-by-address flow
- `sendToChat()` examples (text + file)
- `importFiles()` example
- realtime native + emulation
- `@webxdc/realtime` helper example
- Keep functional parity for examples while allowing project-specific UI changes.

## Build and quality gates

Before completing changes, run:

- `bun run check`
- `bun run build`

For packaging/release changes, also run:

- `bun run package:release`

## Release/versioning constraints

- Keep semantic-release config and CI flow functional.
- Preserve artifact names:
  - `webxdc-svelte-shadcn-template_vX-Y-Z.xdc`
  - `webxdc-svelte-shadcn-template_vX-Y-Z.zip`
- Keep `.xdc` package excluding `webxdc.js`.

## Conventional commits

Use conventional commits (required for semantic-release):

- `feat: ...`
- `fix: ...`
- `docs: ...`
- `refactor: ...`
- `chore: ...`

Use `BREAKING CHANGE:` footer for major bumps.
